Attribution chain
-----------------

1. Original project (upstream of upstream)
   Ankermgmt/ankerctl  -  https://github.com/Ankermgmt/ankerctl
   The original Python "ankerctl" tool and the "libflagship" library that
   reverse-engineered the AnkerMake M5 MQTT, PPPP, and HTTP/Cloud protocols and
   their crypto. Licensed under GPLv3.

2. Go re-implementation (direct upstream of this fork)
   Django1982/ankerctl_go_remake  -  https://github.com/Django1982/ankerctl_go_remake
   A Go port aiming for 1:1 feature parity with the Python original, including
   bit-exact protocol and crypto behavior. Licensed under GPLv3.
   The Go module path of this codebase (github.com/django1982/ankerctl) reflects
   this lineage and is intentionally preserved.

3. This fork
   ankerctl-ng (jr)
   Rebranded "ankerctl-ng" and extended with, among other things:
     - AI print-failure monitoring (saved replies, short-lived evidence images)
     - PPPP upload hardening / self-healing (keepalives, health checks,
       channel-close abort, power-cycle recovery)
     - Smart-socket power-cycle recovery for stuck uploads
     - Home Assistant camera and smart-socket integration
     - Notifications via SMTP, raw webhook, and Apprise; notification history;
       Home Assistant speech hooks
     - Timelapse / camera capture
     - UI changes and an OrcaSlicer-first setup flow

